<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/73.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-20"><hi rend="italic">June 20,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The minister for foreign affairs has requested me to inform you that a
                            communication goes forward by to-day’s mail instructing the Dominican
                            plenipotentiaries to endeavor by every possible effort to effect a
                            satisfactory settlement of the boundary dispute and not to break off
                            negotiations before consulting with the Secretary of State of the United
                            States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>